attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a sample of the Mozi IoT botnet, targeting ARMv7 devices. It exhibits characteristic botnet behavior including vulnerability exploitation, payload downloading, and persistence. IOCs strongly point to Mozi, such as commands to download and execute payloads named `Mozi.m` and `Mozi.a`. The sample establishes persistence by modifying startup scripts like `/etc/rc.d/rc.local` and `/etc/init.d/S95baby.sh`, and remounts the filesystem as read-write (`mount -o remount,rw /overlay /`). It also manipulates `iptables` to block common management ports (e.g., 22, 23, 7547) and uses custom C2 tags like `[/atk]` and `[/dip]`.
